This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the implementation of machine learning algorithms, including deep learning, on resource-constrained mobile embedded devices for image classification tasks. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it deals with model compression and optimization techniques for improving computational efficiency and reducing memory usage. Additionally, it could be categorized under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Embedded Systems (cs.EM) sub-categories as it focuses on implementing deep learning algorithms on embedded devices with limited resources.
